commit.message: Refactor memoryview copying + support overlapping memory
Lower buffer_max_dims to 8
Support atomics in acquisition counting
Optimize indexing when slicing memviews & move to utility
Support index-slicing indirect dimensions if slice data pointer can be moved
Support copy/copy_fortran and is_*_contig methods on memoryview objects
slice assignment + broadcasting leading newaxis dimensions
slice assignment broadcasting & fix some bugs
Test broadcasting with object memoryviews
Fix ellipsis no-op check in AnalyseExpressionsTransform
Support borrowed slices in cdef functions
Optimize with gil blocks
Avoid with gil blocks in memoryview code (for performance)
Fix py24-py25 memoryview compilation errors
Disable intel atomics until it's tested
Fix py32 compatibility & fix warnings
Support copying/slice assigning with dtype object
Support scalar slice assignment
ANSI C compatibility
Don't cast arguments when calling function wrapper (MSVC does not allow casting structs)
Significantly better performing scalar to slice assignment
Fix segfault caused by NULL suboffsets
Initialize allocated cython.array buffer with object dtype to None
Intialize object item pointer properly & C++ compat

title: Atomic acquisition counting, slice assignment (+scalars), overlapping memory, broadcasting, more memoryview object methods, optimized with gil block
